==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek ''dakryo-'', "tear" + ''haima'', "blood" + ''rheein'', "to flow" (or {{prefix|dacry|lang=en}} {{m|en|-o-}} + {{m|en|hemorrhea}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˌdækɹɪəʊheməˈɹɪə/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{label|en|symptom}} The discharge of tears mixed with blood; a hemorrhagic discharge from the lacrimal sac.
# Bloody tears; bleeding from the tear ducts while crying; crying blood.

